<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MATURE TRAVELER: HOTEL DISCOUNTS FROM CALIFORNIA TO FLORIDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HANK KOVELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seniors can take advantage of numerous discounts and deals offered by resorts 
and hotels throughout the United States. Each listing is followed by a 
toll-free phone number through which travelers can make reservations and 
request brochures or other information. 
</P>
<P>
 * In Southern California, near the city of Fallbrook and the Temecula wine 
country in San Diego County, is the Pala Mesa Resort, which has initiated a "55 
Club for Seniors." Those 55 and older can get a guest room for $55, which is 
50% off the regular $110 rate. For golfers, Pala Mesa offers a weekday golf 
package, Sunday through Thursday, which includes a guest room for one night and 
18 holes of golf with greens fee and cart for $55 per person. (Regular rate is 
$69.) Call (800) 722-4700. 
</P>
<P>
 South Seas Plantation, a hotel/ condominium resort on Captiva Island on 
Florida's west coast, near the city of Ft. Myers, is offering a Gold Club 
Holiday package for active seniors. The package is for four days/three nights 
and is loaded with extras, including breakfast for three days, lunch for two, a 
"Tropical Island" dinner, an island cruise and a T-shirt. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, there is a choice of several optional tours, greens fee for nine 
holes of golf, a bike rental, a canoe and other options. The price is 
determined by the room location on the island and the type of room. Until April 
19, the cost for the package ranges $923-$1,107 per couple. In the off-season, 
April 20-Dec. 10, prices range $639-$807 for two persons. Call (800) 237-6000. 
</P>
<P>
 * If you're heading to Kansas City, Mo., the elegant Ritz-Carlton is offering 
a special rate of $119 for two persons, including a continental breakfast each 
morning. Regular rates range $149-$199. The program is valid for an indefinite 
period on a space-available basis. Call (800) 241-3333. 
</P>
<P>
 * The Doubletree group of 55 hotels is offering a 30% discount to seniors who 
are members of AARP, through 1994. All of the Doubletree hotels are in the 
United States, except for one in Windsor, Ontario, Canada. Rates vary, with 
some running as low as $48 per night and others $200 and more, depending on the 
city and season. Doubletree is also offering a 10% discount on food and 
nonalcoholic beverages in its restaurants. The company has already attracted 
attention with its now-traditional welcome gift for guests: freshly baked 
chocolate-chip cookies. For a directory of Doubletree Hotels, call (800) 
222-8733. 
</P>
<P>
 * In Florida, the Biscayne Bay Marriott, on Miami's picturesque waterfront, is 
offering senior rates ranging $80-$99 through April 2, for rooms that are 
usually priced $160-$200 per day. The rate is offered to members of AARP, with 
a 21-day advance purchase. Call (800) 228-9290. 
</P>
</TEXT>
