<P>
BOY, 17, WHO KILLED HIS FAMILY GETS 4 LIFE TERMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teenager who pleaded guilty to killing his father, mother, brother and 
sister received four life terms. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Neugebauer, 17, could be eligible for parole in 24 years with good 
behavior. He had pleaded guilty in October to killing his father. 
</P>
<P>
 Neugebauer said he can't remember killing the rest of his family in January, 
1992, but he pleaded guilty Friday to the other murders, acknowledging that 
prosecutors have enough evidence to convict him. 
</P>
