<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAUCHOS DEFEAT 49ERS AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara continued its mastery over Long Beach State Saturday night 
with an 82-66 Big West Conference victory in the 49ers' campus gym. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gauchos (7-9, 3-3) have won 12 of the last 14 meetings between the 
schools. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach (8-5, 3-3) made 10 of its first 15 field goals and grabbed a 29-18 
lead, but Santa Barbara came back and tied the score at the half, 40-40. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Doug Muse sparked the Gauchos to a 54-44 lead in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach played without starting guard Jeff Rogers, who has an injured leg, 
and backup forward Gerry Branner, who apparently quit the team. PAUL McLEOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
