<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA RALLY ISN'T ENOUGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MITCH POLIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount had its chances Saturday night, only to fall short in a 99-93 
loss to San Diego in a West Coast Conference game before 1,957 at the USD 
Sports Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola (1-14, 0-4) suffered its 16th consecutive road loss and 14th in a row 
in the WCC. 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego (10-5, 2-2) led, 46-35, at halftime and increased its margin to 17 
points early in the second half before the Lions staged a comeback. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lions were led by guard Bill Mazurie with a season high of 23 points and 
forward Wyking Jones with 20. San Diego had five players in double figures, led 
by guard Doug Harris with 20 points. MITCH POLIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
