<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; USC'S LESLIE SCORES 29 POINTS IN VICTORY OVER 
ARIZONA STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lisa Leslie scored 29 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead ninth-ranked USC 
to an 87-81 victory over Arizona State on Saturday night at Tempe, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 The Trojans, 13-1 overall and 6-0 in the Pacific 10 Conference, used a 21-6 
second-half run to build an 80-65 lead with 6:35 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman Tina Thompson scored nine of her 21 points during the run. Karleen 
Shields had a career-high 13 points and added five steals off the bench for 
USC, which was playing without point guard Nicky McCrimmon because of a family 
emergency. 
</P>
<P>
 Nikki Thompson had 28 points and 21 rebounds for Arizona State (2-1, 0-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona 83, UCLA 78 -- The Bruins had a seven-point lead with five minutes to 
play, but the Wildcats used a 20-8 run to rally at Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the first over UCLA in eight tries for Arizona (9-4, 3-2), 
which got 19 points from Kim Conway and 18 from Shawn Coder. The Bruins (8-7, 
3-3) were led by Natalie Williams with 29 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
