<HEADLINE>
<P>
HULA BOWL; FOLEY LEADS COLLEGE ALL-STARS PAST HAWAIIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Glenn Foley of Boston College passed for two touchdowns, leading the College 
All-Stars to a 28-15 victory over the Hawaii All-Stars in the Hula Bowl on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The collegians came back from a 13-point first-half deficit and didn't put the 
game away until Tommy Jones of Fresno State returned an interception 38 yards 
for a touchdown with 2:12 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawaii had taken the lead on field goals of 29 and 42 yards by Zerin Kahn and 
a 19-yard scoring pass from Garrett Gabriel to Daniel Ahuna. 
</P>
<P>
 West Virginia's Jake Kelchner completed a 62-yard scoring pass play to Andre 
Coleman of Kansas State, and Foley gave the collegians a 14-13 halftime lead on 
a nine-yard pass to Florida's Willie Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
 Foley completed 11 of 19 passes for 118 yards, and Kelchner was six of 11 for 
161 yards. 
</P>
