destined to radically outsell the second albums of Jodeci's prime 
competition--Boyz II Men and Color Me Badd. Salt-N-Pepa's album is a strong 
Southern California seller all of a sudden, entering the chart at No. 13. 
"Whatta Man," the second hit single from the female rap crew's album, has 
really boosted album sales. The single premiered on the pop chart at No. 9, 
trailed by "Unity" (No. 10)--by another female rapper, Queen Latifah. TOP 10 
