<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; IRVINE WOMEN BEAT NEVADA, END TWO LOSING STREAKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine women's basketball team ended losing streaks of 11 games overall 
and 12 in the Big West Conference by defeating Nevada, 59-42, Saturday night at 
the Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Jinelle Williams had a game-high 18 points and 12 rebounds for Irvine (2-12, 
1-5), which led, 28-25, at halftime but broke it open early in the second half 
with a 16-2 run. 
</P>
<P>
 Karie Yoshioka added 14 points and Allah-mi Basheer 10 for the Anteaters, 
whose last Big West victory was Feb. 11 over Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Nevada is 3-11 and 0-7. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 62, Southern California 50 -- The Vanguards suffered their 
first conference loss to the undefeated Sunbirds (12-5, 4-0), who took over 
sole possession of first place. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Brannan led Southern California (15-4, 2-1) with 13 points and eight 
rebounds. Tina Demarsh added 11 points and Jamie Zitterkopf 10. 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 81, Cal Baptist 71 -- Gitte Mejer scored 34 points and grabbed 19 
rebounds to lead Concordia (10-7, 2-1), which made seven three-pointers in the 
first half and 10 of 19 in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 85, Cal Baptist 75 -- Augustin Harada led Concordia (13-6, 2-1) with 
18 points on five for six shooting and Craig Martin added 16 points and eight 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 92, Southern California College 75 -- Southern California 
College (9-10, 0-4) remained winless in conference play despite a 22-point 
effort by Danin Bryant. Six players scored in double figures for Fresno 
Pacific, led by Tim Butler's 26 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
