FIRM TO GIVE $10 MILLION IN FOG PILEUP LAWSUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Victims of a fatal 99-vehicle pileup on a foggy stretch of highway will split 
$10 million from a paper plant they partially blame. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowater Inc. agreed to settle 44 lawsuits without admitting responsibility in 
the December, 1990, string of crashes on Interstate 75. The wrecks killed 12 
people and injured more than 50. 
</P>
<P>
 Douglas Fees, an attorney for 30 plaintiffs, said the settlement sends a 
message that companies generating industrial fog need to protect the public. 
</P>
