<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERMISSIBLE LEVELS SET FOR ANTIBIOTICS IN MEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Health Ministry is moving to lift a ban on residual antibiotics and 
antibacterials in beef and pork, in response to demands from the United States 
and Europe. 
</P>
<P>
 In Japan, antibiotics in meats were banned in 1975 and antibacterial residues 
were prohibited in 1979. The bans effectively curtailed meat imports from the 
United States and Europe, which use the banned products in livestock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA012394-0219 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 006498 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
