<P>
YEVGENY IVANOV; RUSSIAN SPY IN PROFUMO SCANDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yevgeny Ivanov, 68, the Russian spy involved in the 1960s Profumo sex scandal 
that nearly brought down the British government.As a Soviet military 
intelligence officer in London in the early 1960s, Ivanov began seeing 
Christine Keeler, who was also sexually involved with John Profumo, the British 
secretary of state for war. When questions were raised about a possible 
security breach, Profumo at first denied knowing Keeler, then admitted to the 
affair and resigned June 5, 1963. Ivanov had been recalled to Moscow in 
December, 1962, months before the scandal broke. He died there Wednesday of 
unannounced causes. 
</P>
