HANDRAILS BADLY NEEDED IN RENOVATED THEATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * We recently went to an open house to see the renovated Alex Theatre in 
Glendale and to check out our season ticket seat locations. 
</P>
<P>
 The design changes and overall decorating are excellent, but there is a major 
flaw. The stairs in the Terrace Section do not have any handrails. These steep 
stairs are reminiscent of those in the upper deck of Dodger Stadium, behind 
home plate. 
</P>
<P>
 How the city of Glendale (which owns the theater) and its building department 
allow this safety hazard to exist is very puzzling. Even if it meets the code, 
common sense dictates that handrails down the middle of the stairs be installed 
immediately, before a tragic accident occurs. 
</P>
<P>
