</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On the 21st anniversary of the Supreme Court's Roe vs. Wade decision, about 
200 anti-abortion protesters knelt outside the White House to pray for 
President Clinton, his wife and top Administration officials."We pray that you 
will deliver our nation from this hand of tyranny. We pray, our God, that you 
will invade this mansion," intoned the Rev. Paul Schenck of Buffalo, N.Y. The 
First Family was spending the weekend at the presidential retreat at Camp 
David, Md. The abortion opponents complain that Clinton's health care reform 
package would cover abortion on demand. 
