<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPLIANCE WORKER ARRESTED IN ALLEGED MURDER ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An employee at an Orange County appliance store was arrested on suspicion of 
attempted murder Saturday after he allegedly shot a customer with whom he had 
argued inside the store. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a situation that just went way out of control," Garden Grove Police 
Sgt. Joe Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson said the dispute began when the employee, identified as Andrew Ban, 
waited on a customer just before taking a lunch break at the Orange County 
Appliance Parts store in the 10000 block of Stanford Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not know the reason for the argument, but said it spilled into the 
store's parking lot about 12:35 p.m., when customer James Vincent Lannon 
followed Ban outside to his car. The customer allegedly yanked Ban out of the 
car and began fighting with him. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson said Ban then pulled out a .38-caliber revolver and fired one shot, 
hitting Lannon in the leg. Both men were still at the scene when police 
arrived. 
</P>
<P>
 Ban, 30, of Huntington Beach, was taken into custody. Lannon, 37, of Corona, 
was transported to UCI Medical Center, where he was listed in stable condition. 
</P>
