<HEADLINE>
<P>
OF CANALS, CRUISES AND COUNTRYSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To cruise the Erie Canal at 10 m.p.h. is to see New York in a whole new 
light.The inland waterway stretches through some of central New York's 
prettiest countryside and is part of the 524-mile New York State Canal System. 
Rent a fully equipped canal boat and chart your own course for a week or take a 
two-hour cruise. Bike or hike along a towpath. Visit one of the parks, 
restaurants, inns, museums or historic sites that line the banks or are close 
by. It's all described in a new, free brochure that will "Unlock the Legend" of 
the canals. To obtain a copy, write: New York State Canal Corp., P.O. Box 189, 
Albany, N.Y. 12201. 
</P>
</TEXT>
