<HEADLINE>
<P>
A MATTER OF TASTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We have to wonder whether David Haldane really knows good Mexican food after 
reading his comments on Mi Casa in Cabo San Lucas ("Econo-Dive," Jan. 2). 
</P>
<P>
 We have traveled extensively in Mexico for more than a decade and . . . 
recently spent a week in Cabo San Lucas.Out of seven nights, we ate at Mi Casa 
three and at Ponchos three; the other night at the charming Hotel Hacienda. 
True, Mi Casa may be expensive, but it is more than worth it. They feature 
sauces from all parts of Mexico. You don't go there to eat an enchilada! The 
only place where we were unhappy with the food was our hotel -- the lovely 
Pueblo Bonito -- because it was too Americanized and poor quality. Very 
surprising because everything else is tops. 
</P>
<P>
 We're ready to return to Cabo so we can enjoy Mi Casa's fine cuisine. 
</P>
<P>
 MR. and MRS. I.B. MERLES 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 
</P>
