<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE 6.6 QUAKE; ON THE REBOUND: A GUIDE TO RECOVERY AND RESOURCES; SPECIAL 
ASSISTANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Habitat for Humanity of San Fernando/Santa Clarita Valleys has a program to 
help low-income homeowners repair their dwellings. No profit/zero interest 
loans are available for qualifying homeowners who have minor to moderate damage 
-- broken windows, damaged porches, pipes and chimneys -- and those who have 
major repairs.Homeowner must help with repairs. The organization also has a new 
housing program that requires a 1% down payment. Homeowner must help with the 
work. For more information, contact: Habitat for Humanity of San Fernando/Santa 
Clarita Valleys, P.O. Box 710, North Hollywood 91603; (818) 980-9797 
</P>
<P>
 * A One-Stop Post-Earthquake Permit Center will open Monday to assist county 
residents in their efforts to rebuild damaged structures in the Santa Clarita 
Valley. The center will be at 23757 Valencia Blvd., Valencia. It will be 
staffed by representatives of the Fire Department and Building and Safety/Land 
Development Division of the county Department of Public Works from Monday 
through Friday, and with representatives of the Health and Regional Planning 
departments on Mondays and Wednesdays. The hours will be 8 a.m.-4:30 p.m. The 
center will provide information to homeowners on rebuilding and will streamline 
the permit process by allowing an applicant to receive all necessary agency 
approvals at one location. 
</P>
</TEXT>
