COMMUNITY NEWS: CENTRAL: DOWNTOWN; FORUM ON CRIME'S EFFECT ON BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Crime's effect on the business community will be discussed at a Wednesday 
lunchtime forum at the Los Angeles Area Chamber of Commerce office, 404 S. 
Bixel St. 
</P>
<P>
 Scheduled to speak are Deputy Police Chief Mark Kroeker, a specialist in 
community-based policing; Peter Greenwood, a senior researcher at the RAND 
Corp. and head of its criminal justice program, and Municipal Court Judge 
Rudolph A. Diaz. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to a general discussion of forgery, shoplifting and other crimes 
that affect businesses, the talks will include the perceived and statistical 
levels of local crime, employee safety and the effect additional police 
officers could have on business ledgers. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets to the forum are $23.50, including lunch.  
</P>
