<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-WILSHIRE; HIV COUNCIL INVITES NEW PARTICIPANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAKE DOHERTY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The HIV Health Services Planning Council will sponsor two orientations next 
month to explain how people with HIV -- or who are at risk of infection -- can 
participate in the council and its task forces. 
</P>
<P>
 The council, established by the County Board of Supervisors, is responsible 
for setting program and funding priorities for many HIV services in the 
county.The council's office is at 600 S. Commonwealth Ave. on the sixth floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members determine which communities within the county require 
particular attention and recommend how the $30 million should be distributed 
among education and prevention programs and outpatient services. 
</P>
<P>
 The sessions are scheduled from noon to 5 p.m. Feb. 3 and from 9 a.m. to 2 
p.m. Feb. 4 at Orthopaedic Hospital, 2400 S. Flower St. Lunch will be provided 
at both sessions. Participants need attend only one session and seating is 
limited to 60. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations should be made by Jan. 31. Contact Nancy Salem at (213) 351-8044 
or (213) 351-8022. JAKE DOHERTY 
</P>
</TEXT>
