<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSPECTION TAG'S COLORS DEMYSTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the aftermath of Monday's earthquake, anyone concerned about the condition 
of their home or business can look for placards posted by the city Department 
of Building and Safety indicating that an inspection has been done. The 
18-by-24-inch placards are in three colors:  
</P>
<P>
 * Green placards indicate it is safe to enter and occupy a building; 
</P>
<P>
 * Red placards indicate that the building is unsafe and should not be entered; 
</P>
<P>
 * Yellow placards indicate entry is restricted; occupants may enter at their 
own risk to gather belongings, but may not stay and occupy the building. 
</P>
<P>
 Specific restrictions are indicated on yellow placards. For instance, the 
restriction may only apply to one part of a building. 
</P>
<P>
 The placards generally are posted at main entrances. 
</P>
</TEXT>
