<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAKE-RELIEF INFORMATION LINE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Rescate has set up an earthquake-relief information line for residents who 
have questions about city, state and federal assistance. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to act as a clearinghouse for people who need help," said Oscar 
Andrade, executive director of the Pico-Union social service agency. 
</P>
<P>
 El Rescate will have contact numbers for the Federal Emergency Management 
Agency, the Los Angeles Police Department, the city Building and Safety 
Department and Department of Water and Power. Residents can call weekdays from 
9 a.m. to 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 387-3284. 
</P>
